{{see|bo}}

==English==
===Etymology===
Of Scandinavian origin. Old Norse [[bua]] = 'to build, live, dwell'; Swedish verb 'att [[bo]]' = 'to live, dwell'; Swedish noun [[bo]] = 'dweller; dwelling' cf. Stockholmbo = 'dweller in Stockholm'.

This name could also be a variant writing of the given name [[Beau]]. The name Beau comes from the French word [[beau]] = 'beautiful'. Cf. French Isabeau, side form of Isabelle.

